e is not a servant of ideology. Themes of family, exile, the tango, Argentina, and Gelman's Jewish heritage resonate throughout his poems, works that celebrate life while confronting heartache and loss."remembering their little bones when it rains/ the compañerosstomp on darkness/set forth from death/wander the tender night/I hear their voices like living faces"—from Remembering Their Little Bones  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  a20th century argentine literature.  a20th century latin american literature.  aargentine literature.  aargentine military government.  aargentine poet.  aargentine poetry.  abrutality.  acervantes prize.  adignity.  adirty war.  adisappeared.  aepic.  ahuman spirit.  ajewish heritage.  ajuan rulfo award.  alatin american literature.  alatin american poetry.  amilitary junta.  apolitical exile.  apolitical literature.  apolitics of argentina.  apostcolonialism.  asocial commentary.  asocial conscience.  astruggles.  atenderness.  atranslated poetry.  atranslated text.1 aGaleano, Eduardo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLindgren, Joan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052020587140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520918023?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520918023423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520918023/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY